steps: Preheat the oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Lightly coat a baking dish with cooking spray.. Season chicken evenly with 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon pepper, and onion powder. steps: Heat oil in an extra-large skillet over medium heat. Add panko and garlic powder. Cook, stirring, until toasted, 2 to 3 minutes. Transfer to a shallow dish and let cool, 2 to 3 minutes. steps: Mix chicken, red onion, celery, salt, black pepper, cayenne pepper, smoked paprika, cumin, and mayonnaise until well blended. Cover and refrigerate until thoroughly chilled, at least 30 minutes.. Working one at a time, dip a rice paper into cold water and let soak just until it starts to become flexible. Shake off most of the excess water and lay on a work surface. Place 2 slices of avocado in the center of the wrapper, about 1 inch in from the edge closest to you. name: Grilled Pineapple Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 fluid ounce) can or bottle', 'name': 'beer'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh rosemary, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly cracked black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'chicken breast tenderloins'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'fresh pineapple'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) bag', 'name': 'baby spinach leaves'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pine nuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'mandarin oranges, drained'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'poppy seed salad dressing (such as Kraft®), or to taste'}
steps: Mix beer, honey, Dijon mustard, olive oil, rosemary, garlic powder, salt, and black pepper in a large resealable plastic bag until thoroughly combined. Add chicken to the marinade, evenly coat, and squeeze air from the bag. Seal and refrigerate several hours to overnight, turning bag over occasionally.. Preheat outdoor grill for medium-high heat and lightly oil the grate.. Twist top from pineapple and cut peel off in long vertical strips. Cut pineapple into wedges vertically and cut the tough core from each wedge.. Thread marinated chicken tenders onto skewers. Grill chicken and pineapple wedges on the preheated grill until chicken is no longer pink inside, chicken juices run clear, and pineapple wedges are tender and show light brown grill marks, 10 to 12 minutes. Cut chicken and pineapple into bite-sized pieces.. Toss spinach with pine nuts and mandarin orange segments in a large bowl. Top salad with chicken and pineapple pieces. Serve on salad plates; drizzle each serving with 2 teaspoons poppy seed dressing.
